As India celebrates its 75th anniversary of independence, the United States joins in honoring its democratic journey. The partnership between the two countries is grounded in a shared commitment to the rule of law and the promotion of human freedom and dignity. The Indian-American community in the United States has contributed to innovation and strength. The two democracies will continue to work together to defend the rules-based order, promote peace and prosperity, advance a free and open Indo-Pacific, and address global challenges.